a, 1973, 1986).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,402,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">
In this paper, 
<number box="[353,381,619,643]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="12.0">12</number>
species, excluding five known Oriental species, are recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1138,1238,618,643]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">Thailand</collectingCountry>
for the first time, of which 
<number box="[263,291,655,679]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="10.0">10</number>
are new to science. Most of the flies described and discussed below belong to a group of shining coppery-greenish, black species that occur throughout the Old World tropics. Only six species, 
<taxonomicName box="[1220,1332,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancyla" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1220,1332,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. ancyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1340,1428,690,715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1340,1366,690,715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1380,1422,690,715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Sasakawa, M." authorityName="Sasakawa, M." box="[151,458,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gressitti">
<emphasis box="[151,283,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. gressitti</emphasis>
Sasakawa, 
<taxonomicName box="[427,458,727,750]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lunulata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[427,458,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicName>
lunulata 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[577,671,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[577,603,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[623,665,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[692,869,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pandiculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[692,869,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. pandiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[882,977,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[882,908,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[929,971,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Meijere" authorityName="Meijere" box="[998,1260,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="provecta">
<emphasis box="[998,1138,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. provecta</emphasis>
(Meijere)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Sasakawa" authorityName="Sasakawa" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yodai">
<emphasis box="[1330,1436,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. yodai</emphasis>
Sasakawa
</taxonomicName>
, lack the coppery-greenish sheen on the mesoscutum and abdomen. The color of the fringe on the calypter, which is either white to yellowish-white or brown to black, is an essential differentiating character among the species. The pale fringe is seen in most of the 
<collectingCountry box="[717,817,834,859]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">Thailand</collectingCountry>
species, and only seven species have a dark fringe: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancyla" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. ancyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[233,322,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[233,259,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[274,316,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[337,475,870,895]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catalexis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[337,475,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. catalexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[482,570,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[482,565,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[586,712,871,894]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gressitti">
<emphasis box="[586,712,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. gressitti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[727,858,870,895]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lunulata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[727,858,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. lunulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[866,954,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[866,892,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[907,949,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Sasakawa, M." authorityName="Sasakawa, M." box="[970,1295,870,895]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malayensis">
<emphasis box="[970,1132,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. malayensis</emphasis>
Sasakawa, 
<taxonomicName box="[1264,1295,871,894]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pandiculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1264,1295,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicName>
pandiculata 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,240,906,931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,177,906,931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,234,906,931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[305,440,908,931]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="provecta">
<emphasis box="[305,440,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. provecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The males of some species with a pale fringe can be further characterized by eyes that are whitish-pilose on the anterodorsal area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,402,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">
This is the dominant genus in 
<collectingCountry box="[540,640,978,1003]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">Thailand</collectingCountry>
as well as in other Oriental countries. It is also notable that 
<number box="[1319,1347,978,1003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="16.0">16</number>
species of 
<number box="[183,211,1014,1039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="25.0">25</number>
known species are treated here as endemic, although some of them will likely be found in other Oriental- Oceanian countries in due course.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,402,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">
Special attention should be drawn to both thoracic coloration and male genitalic features in the following species. Firstly, three of the new species, 
<taxonomicName box="[617,755,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catalexis">
<emphasis box="[617,755,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. catalexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[770,854,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[202,1374,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[197,1379,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 18. Male genitalia of Melanagromyza catalexis sp. nov. (9 – 11, holotype), M. cirrappendicula sp. nov. (12 – 14, holotype) and M. lunulata sp. nov. (15 – 18, holotype). 9, 12, 15, surstylus; 10, 13, 16, phallus, lateral view; 11, 14, 17, phallus, ventral view; 18, ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216907/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">
Fig. 
<number box="[823,854,1123,1147]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[875,969,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lunulata">
<emphasis box="[875,969,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">lunulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[983,1065,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[202,1374,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[197,1379,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 18. Male genitalia of Melanagromyza catalexis sp. nov. (9 – 11, holotype), M. cirrappendicula sp. nov. (12 – 14, holotype) and M. lunulata sp. nov. (15 – 18, holotype). 9, 12, 15, surstylus; 10, 13, 16, phallus, lateral view; 11, 14, 17, phallus, ventral view; 18, ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216907/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">
Fig. 
<number box="[1036,1065,1122,1147]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[1129,1263,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pandiculata">
<emphasis box="[1129,1263,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">pandiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1278,1362,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 36" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,197,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1816]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 36. Male genitalia of Melanagromyza pandiculata sp. nov. (30 – 32, holotype) and M. sexseriata sp. nov. (33 – 36, holotype)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216909/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">
Fig. 
<number box="[1331,1362,1123,1147]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
), have a distinct phallus with a membranous swelling on ventral side. It indicates a close relationship with the following species: Palaearctic, Oriental, Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName authority="Hendel" authorityName="Hendel" box="[650,898,1194,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis box="[650,806,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. pubescens</emphasis>
Hendel
</taxonomicName>
(
<number box="[917,977,1195,1219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="1923.0">1923</number>
; Sasakawa 
