<number box="[870,930,1410,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="1996.0">1996</number>
: fig. 
<number box="[992,1009,1411,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="2.0">2</number>
; Spencer 
<number box="[1125,1185,1410,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="1964.0">1964</number>
: fig. 
<number box="[1247,1279,1411,1435]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="23.0">23</number>
). Thirdly, the basiphallus is divided distinctly into two forms: short tubiform in 
<taxonomicName box="[883,983,1446,1471]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catalexis">
<emphasis box="[883,983,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">catalexis</emphasis>
