and 
<taxonomicName box="[1036,1117,1446,1471]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luthulii">
<emphasis box="[1036,1117,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">luthulii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and U-shaped with sidearm variable in length and shape in other many species. These phallic characters are probably apomorphic.
